"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-01-andy-murray-tennis-retirement-confirmed-playing-last-match-olympics-20531775\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Andy Murrayhas officially confirmed his retirement from tennis after playing his final professional match at the 2024Olympic Gamesin Paris.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 139, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 133, \"end\": 138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.666071205104717e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Murray played a total of 1001 singles matches and revealed ahead of the Games that itwould be his 'last ever tennis tournament'- with his quarter-final men's doubles defeat next toDan Evanson Thursday meaning it is now all over.\", \"from\": 141, \"to\": 369, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 141, \"end\": 147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.875625727295227e-51, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Taylor Fritz and Tommy Paul beat Murray and Evans 6-2 6-4, with the British duo unable to follow up on theirtwo rollercoaster victoriesover Japan and Belgium.\", \"from\": 371, \"to\": 529, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 371, \"end\": 383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Fritz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Taylor Fritz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Fritz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Fritz\"}, {\"begin\": 388, \"end\": 398, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Paul\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8297620508041343e-23, \"text\": \"Tommy Paul\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Paul\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Paul\"}, {\"begin\": 404, \"end\": 410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.875625727295227e-51, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 415, \"end\": 420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DaBaby\", \"score\": 0.9962764751012816, \"rank\": 0.003737441354857752, \"text\": \"Evans\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DaBaby\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DaBaby\"}, {\"begin\": 439, \"end\": 446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"score\": 0.9996660470955422, \"rank\": 0.00032846679965998447, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\"}, {\"begin\": 511, \"end\": 516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_Davis_Cup_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999818101, \"rank\": 1.4247457663441902e-11, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_Davis_Cup_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_Davis_Cup_team\"}, {\"begin\": 521, \"end\": 528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_Billie_Jean_King_Cup_team\", \"score\": 0.7799626097273504, \"rank\": 0.2762317913757712, \"text\": \"Belgium\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_Billie_Jean_King_Cup_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium_Billie_Jean_King_Cup_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'I am proud of my career, my achievements and what I put into the sport,' Murray said after his last dance in the French capital.\", \"from\": 531, \"to\": 660, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 605, \"end\": 611, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.875625727295227e-51, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 645, \"end\": 651, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.4854647398009583, \"rank\": 0.7788525436925454, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Obviously it was emotional because it's the last time I will play.\", \"from\": 661, \"to\": 728, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But I am genuinely happy now.\", \"from\": 729, \"to\": 758, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am happy with how it finished.\", \"from\": 759, \"to\": 791, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am glad I got to go out here at the Olympics and finish on my terms.'\", \"from\": 792, \"to\": 863, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Widely regarded as one of Great Britain's biggest sporting heroes, Murray hangs up his racket and has called time on his career with twoWimbledontitles, two Olympic gold medals, theUSOpen and the Davis Cup in his trophy cabinet.\", \"from\": 865, \"to\": 1093, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 891, \"end\": 904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_Davis_Cup_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.892289561165865e-20, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_Davis_Cup_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_Davis_Cup_team\"}, {\"begin\": 932, \"end\": 938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.875625727295227e-51, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 37-year-oldended Britain's 77-year waitfor a Wimbledon men's singles champion in 2013, which sparked emotional scenes up and down the country.\", \"from\": 1095, \"to\": 1241, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1116, \"end\": 1123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9992663410247556, \"rank\": 0.0007339618877097328, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He struggled badly with injuries in his twilight years but made a shock comeback with a metal hip and remarkably went on to land even more silverware.\", \"from\": 1243, \"to\": 1393, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Murray picked up a nasty back problem at Queen's Club in June, which required surgery and forced him out of one last appearance in the Wimbledon singles, althoughhe did get an emotional farewell playing doubleswith his brother Jamie.\", \"from\": 1395, \"to\": 1628, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1395, \"end\": 1401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.875625727295227e-51, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He had been hoping to play Olympic singles but, again, could not get himself fit enough as he decided to solely focus on the doubles with fellow Brit Evans.\", \"from\": 1630, \"to\": 1786, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1780, \"end\": 1785, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DaBaby\", \"score\": 0.9962764751012816, \"rank\": 0.003737441354857752, \"text\": \"Evans\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DaBaby\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DaBaby\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Murray registered a total of 46 career titles in singles, which puts him 15th overall in the Open Era.\", \"from\": 1788, \"to\": 1890, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1788, \"end\": 1794, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.875625727295227e-51, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He stands alone as\\u00a0the first tennis player - and only man in history - to win Olympic gold singles medals on two different surfaces.\", \"from\": 1891, \"to\": 2023, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Heenjoyed 41 weeks as the world No.1, a sensational feat given the era of tennis he was playing in withNovak Djokovic, Rafael Nadal and Roger Federer.\", \"from\": 2025, \"to\": 2175, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2134, \"end\": 2142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 0.999999950986877, \"rank\": 4.9013346725412464e-08, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}, {\"begin\": 2144, \"end\": 2156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rafael Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}, {\"begin\": 2161, \"end\": 2174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Federer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Roger Federer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Federer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roger_Federer\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Murrayguided Britain to glory in the Davis Cuptoo, ending the country's 79-year wait to lift the trophy, with 2015 marking the team's first triumph since 1936.\", \"from\": 2177, \"to\": 2336, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2190, \"end\": 2197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9992663410247556, \"rank\": 0.0007339618877097328, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Murray, who also won Olympic silver alongside Laura Robson in mixed doubles and was a finalist at the other two Grand Slams he did not win - Roland-Garros and the Australian Open - has struggled with various injury problems since 2016and it looked like his career was overbefore he successfully returned with a metal hip.\", \"from\": 2338, \"to\": 2659, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2338, \"end\": 2344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.875625727295227e-51, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 2384, \"end\": 2396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Robson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laura Robson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Robson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laura_Robson\"}, {\"begin\": 2479, \"end\": 2492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.488880785954864e-12, \"text\": \"Roland-Garros\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After making a comeback, Murray worked his way back into the world top 50, won the European Open, reached three more ATP Tour finals, won the Queen's Club doubles title and lifted three trophies on the lower-level ATP Challenger Tour.\", \"from\": 2661, \"to\": 2895, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2686, \"end\": 2692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.875625727295227e-51, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 2875, \"end\": 2894, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ATP_Challenger_Tour\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.071102126359592e-32, \"text\": \"ATP Challenger Tour\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ATP_Challenger_Tour\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/ATP_Challenger_Tour\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Murray confirmed in July 2023 that he was starting to think about retirement and in February this year,he announced that 2024 was 'likely'going to be his final summer in tennis, with the Olympics in Paris to beone of his last events.\", \"from\": 2897, \"to\": 3130, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2897, \"end\": 2903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.875625727295227e-51, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 3096, \"end\": 3101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.666071205104717e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In March,Murray suffered an ankle injury-admitting that he would be ruled out for an 'extended period'- but returned in time for the French Open.\", \"from\": 3132, \"to\": 3277, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3141, \"end\": 3147, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.875625727295227e-51, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was set to play Wimbledon singles before his back injury at Queen's Club in June but was only fit enough for doubles.\", \"from\": 3278, \"to\": 3398, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After the Olympic doubles, he's now officially retired.\", \"from\": 3399, \"to\": 3454, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Andy Murray 'definitely' sees himself having 'some involvement' in tennis going forward.\", \"from\": 3456, \"to\": 3544, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He has previouslyexpressed an interest in entering a coaching career.\", \"from\": 3545, \"to\": 3614, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For now, though, the British sporting legend is going to take some time away to focus on his family.\", \"from\": 3616, \"to\": 3716, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3637, \"end\": 3644, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"score\": 0.9996660470955422, \"rank\": 0.00032846679965998447, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Ultimately, the decision had to come from me,' Murray toldCNNlast week about his retirement from professional tennis.\", \"from\": 3718, \"to\": 3836, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3766, \"end\": 3772, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.875625727295227e-51, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'I am happy that I get to finish playing an Olympics with a lot of my\\u2026 I consider a lot of the tennis players on our team close friends of mine.\", \"from\": 3837, \"to\": 3981, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'Getting to be around them [makes me happy] and I have great memories from the Olympics.\", \"from\": 3983, \"to\": 4071, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not know exactly what my legacy is\\u2026 and I do not feel like it's for me to decide that, it's more for others.\", \"from\": 4072, \"to\": 4185, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And what's next - initially, I am going to go home and I am going to spend time with my family and be around my kids.\", \"from\": 4186, \"to\": 4303, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'I have four young children which, I want to be at home for them and I want to avoid the long weeks of traveling and being away from that.\", \"from\": 4305, \"to\": 4443, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I found that hard the last few years.\", \"from\": 4444, \"to\": 4481, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'I want to be home with them and take some time to relax and recover and have a think about what it is that I want to do, what it is that I want to do next.\", \"from\": 4483, \"to\": 4639, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I definitely still see myself having some involvement in tennis.\", \"from\": 4640, \"to\": 4704, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And I am looking forward to something new now.\", \"from\": 4705, \"to\": 4751, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But I am not entirely sure of what that new is yet.'\", \"from\": 4752, \"to\": 4804, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ArrowMORE:Fans evacuated from Olympic venue but LeBron James is allowed to stay and watch  ArrowMORE:Olympic tennis ball girl goes viral for giving Novak Djokovic a flirty look  ArrowMORE:Andy Murray heartbroken to miss out on 'fairytale ending' at Paris Olympics  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.\", \"from\": 4806, \"to\": 5181, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4854, \"end\": 4866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LeBron James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}, {\"begin\": 4954, \"end\": 4968, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Novak Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}, {\"begin\": 4994, \"end\": 5005, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.464658342583544e-74, \"text\": \"Andy Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 5055, \"end\": 5069, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 5071, \"end\": 5077, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punchy,_Somme\", \"score\": 0.6784377202964147, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Punchy\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punchy,_Somme\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punchy,_Somme\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply.\", \"from\": 5183, \"to\": 5314, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.\", \"from\": 5315, \"to\": 5487, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5377, \"end\": 5383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punchy,_Somme\", \"score\": 0.6784377202964147, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Punchy\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punchy,_Somme\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punchy,_Somme\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply.\", \"from\": 5489, \"to\": 5620, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy\", \"from\": 5621, \"to\": 5681, \"entities\": []}]}"